<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 1027/97 of 6 June 1997 determining, for the 1997 marketing year, the estimated loss of income and the estimated level of the premium payable per ewe and per female goat and fixing the first advance payment for this premium and an advance payment of the specific aid for sheep and goat farming in certain less favoured areas of the Community </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1027/97, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks 1997. majandusaasta hinnanguline saamata j&auml;&auml;v tulu ning ute ja emaskitse kohta makstava lisatasu hinnanguline m&auml;&auml;r ning m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks k&otilde;nealuse lisatasu esimene ettemakse ja teatavates &uuml;henduse ebasoodsamates piirkondades lamba- ja kitsekasvatuseks etten&auml;htud eriabi ettemakse 6. juuni 1997 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89 of 25 September 1989 on the common organization of the market in sheepmeat and goatmeat (1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1589/96 (2), and in particular Article 5 (6) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 25. septembri 1989. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 lamba- ja kitselihaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1589/96, (2) eriti selle artikli 5 l&otilde;iget 6, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Regulation (EEC) No 1601/92 of 15 June 1992 concerning specific measures for the Canary Islands with regard to certain agricultural products (3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 2348/96 (4), and in particular Article 13 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse 15. juuni 1992. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1601/92 Kanaari saarte heaks teatavate p&otilde;llumajandussaaduste suhtes kohaldatavate erimeetmete kohta, (3) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2348/96, (4) eriti selle artiklit 13, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 5 (1) and (5) of Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89 provides for the grant of a premium to compensate for any loss of income sustained by producers of sheepmeat and, in certain areas, of goatmeat; whereas those areas are defined in Annex I to Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89 and in Article 1 of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1065/86 of 11 April 1986 determining the mountain areas in which the premium for goatmeat is granted (5), as amended by Regulation (EEC) No 3519/86 (6); </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 artikli 5 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 5 n&auml;hakse ette lisatasu andmine lambaliha ja teatavatel aladel kitseliha tootjatele saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulu h&uuml;vitamiseks; k&otilde;nealused alad on m&auml;&auml;ratletud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 I lisas ja komisjoni 11. aprilli 1986. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 1065/86, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks m&auml;gipiirkonnad, kus antakse kitseliha tootjatele lisatasu, (5) muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 3519/86; (6) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to Article 5 (6) of Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89 and to enable an advance payment to be made to sheepmeat and goatmeat producers, the foreseeable loss of income should be estimated in the light of the foreseeable trend in market prices; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 6 kohaselt ning v&otilde;imaldamaks teha ettemakseid lambaliha ja kitseliha tootjatele, tuleks prognoositavat saamata j&auml;&auml;vat tulu hinnata vastavalt prognoositavale turuhindade suundumusele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to Article 5 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89, the amount of the premium per ewe for producers of heavy lambs is obtained by multiplying the loss of income referred to in the second subparagraph of paragraph 1 of that Article by a coefficient expressing the annual average production of heavy lamb meat per ewe producing these lambs expressed per 100 kilograms of carcase weight; whereas the coefficient for 1997 has not yet been fixed in view of the lack of full Community statistics; whereas, pending the fixing of that coefficient, a provisional coefficient should be used; whereas Article 5 (3) of that Regulation also fixes the amount per ewe for producers of light lambs and per female of the caprine species and at 80 % of the premium per ewe for producers of heavy lambs; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 2 kohaselt saadakse raskete tallede tootjatele makstav lisatasu ute kohta k&otilde;nealuse artikli l&otilde;ike 1 teises l&otilde;igus viidatud saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulu korrutamisel koefitsiendiga, mis v&auml;ljendab aasta keskmist raskete tallede toodangut raskeid tallesid tootva ute kohta 100 kg r&uuml;mpade puhul; &uuml;henduse t&auml;ieliku statistika puudumise t&otilde;ttu ei ole 1997. aasta koefitsienti veel kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ratud; k&otilde;nealuse koefitsiendi kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramiseni tuleks kasutada ajutist koefitsienti; k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 3 m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks ka kergete tallede tootjate lisatasu ute kohta ning kitsekasvatajate lisatasu emaskitse kohta; lisatasu on 80% raskete tallede tootjatele ute kohta makstavast lisatasust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to Article 8 of Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89, the premium must be reduced by the impact on the basic price of the coefficient provided for in paragraph 2 of that Article; whereas that coefficient is fixed by Article 8 (4) at 7 %; </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 artiklile 8 tuleb lisatasu v&auml;hendada k&otilde;nealuse artikli l&otilde;ikes 2 etten&auml;htud koefitsiendi m&otilde;ju v&otilde;rra baashinnale; k&otilde;nealuseks koefitsiendiks on artikli 8 l&otilde;ikega 4 m&auml;&auml;ratud 7%; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in accordance with Article 5 (6) of Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89, the half-yearly advance payment is fixed at 30 % of the expected premium; whereas, in accordance with Article 4 (3) of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2700/93 (7), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1526/96 (8), the advance payment is to be paid only if it is equal to or greater than ECU 1; </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 artikli 5 l&otilde;ikele 6 on poolaasta ettemakseks m&auml;&auml;ratud 30% etten&auml;htud lisatasust; vastavalt komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2700/93 (7) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1526/96 (8)) artikli 4 l&otilde;ikele 3 tehakse ettemakse ainult juhul, kui selle suurus on v&auml;hemalt 1 ek&uuml;&uuml;; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the agricultural conversion rate has been frozen until 1 January 1999 for certain currencies by Council Regulation (EC) No 1527/95 (9); </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rusele (E&Uuml;) nr 1527/95 (9) on p&otilde;llumajanduslikud &uuml;mberarvestuskursid teatavate omav&auml;&auml;ringute suhtes k&uuml;lmutatud kuni 1. jaanuarini 1999; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, under Regulation (EEC) No 1323/90 (10), as last amended by Commission Regulation (EC) No 40/96 (11), the Council instituted specific aid for sheep and goat farming in certain less-favoured areas of the Community; whereas it lays down that the aid is to be granted under the same conditions as those for the grant of the premium for producers of sheepmeat and goatmeat; whereas, in view of the present uncertainty of the market situation in certain Member States, the Member States should be authorized, for the 1997 marketing year, to pay immediately an amount equal to 90 % of the aid; </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt m&auml;&auml;rusele (EM&Uuml;) nr 1323/90, (10) viimati muudetud komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 40/96, (11) on n&otilde;ukogu sisse seadnud lamba- ja kitsekasvatuse eriabi &uuml;henduse teatavates ebasoodsamates piirkondades; k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatakse, et abi antakse samadel tingimustel, mille alusel m&auml;&auml;ratakse lisatasu lamba- ja kitseliha tootjatele; silmas pidades turuolukorra praegust ebakindlust teatavates liikmesriikides, tuleks lubada liikmesriikidel 1997. majandusaasta abisummast viivitamatult v&auml;lja maksta 90%; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Regulation (EEC) No 1601/92 provides for the application of specific measures relating to agricultural production in the Canary Islands; whereas those measures entail the grant of a supplement to the ewe premium to producers of light lambs and she-goats on the same conditions as those governing the grant of the premium referred to in Article 5 of Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89; whereas those conditions provide that Spain is authorized to pay an advance on the said supplementary premium; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 1601/92 s&auml;testatakse erimeetmete kohaldamine seoses p&otilde;llumajandustootmisega Kanaari saartel; k&otilde;nealused meetmed annavad kergete tallede ja emaskitsede tootjatele &otilde;iguse saada t&auml;iendavat lisatasu emaslooma kohta samadel tingimustel kui need, millele on osutatud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 artiklis 5 etten&auml;htud lisatasu andmise puhul; nende tingimuste kohaselt on Hispaanial lubatud teha k&otilde;nealuse t&auml;iendava lisatasu ettemakseid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Sheep and Goats, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las lamba- ja kitselihaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> A difference is hereby estimated between the basic price, reduced by the impact of the coefficient laid down in Article 8 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89, and the foreseeable market price during 1997 is ECU 102,785 per 100 kg. </inglise>
<eesti> Hinnanguline erinevus m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 artikli 8 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud koefitsiendi m&otilde;ju v&otilde;rra v&auml;hendatud baashinna ning 1997. aasta prognoositava turuhinna vahel on 102,785 ek&uuml;&uuml;d 100 kg kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The estimated amount of the premium payable per ewe is as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> Ute kohta makstava lisatasu hinnanguline suurus on j&auml;rgmine: </eesti>
<inglise> - producers of heavy lambs: ECU 16,446, </inglise>
<eesti> - raskete tallede tootjad: 16,446 ek&uuml;&uuml;d, </eesti>
<inglise> - producers of light lambs: ECU 13,157. </inglise>
<eesti> - kergete tallede tootjad: 13,157 ek&uuml;&uuml;d. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Pursuant to Article 5 (6) of Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89, the first advance that the Member States are authorized to pay to producers shall be as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 6 kohaselt on esimene ettemakse, mis liikmesriikidel on lubatud tootjatele maksta, j&auml;rgmine: </eesti>
<inglise> - producers of heavy lambs: ECU 4,934 per lamb, </inglise>
<eesti> - raskete tallede tootjad: 4,934 ek&uuml;&uuml;d lambatalle kohta, </eesti>
<inglise> - producers of light lambs: ECU 3,947 per lamb. </inglise>
<eesti> - kergete tallede tootjad: 3,947 ek&uuml;&uuml;d lambatalle kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The estimated amount of the premium payable per female of the caprine species in the areas designated in Annex I to Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89 and in Article 1 of Regulation (EEC) No 1065/86: ECU 13,157. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 I lisas ja m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1065/86 artiklis 1 m&auml;&auml;ratletud piirkondades makstava lisatasu hinnanguline suurus emaskitse kohta on 13,157 ek&uuml;&uuml;d. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Pursuant to Article 5 (6) of Regulation (EEC) No 3013/89, the first advance which the Member States are authorized to pay to goatmeat producers located in the areas designated in paragraph 1 shall be as follows: ECU 3,947 per female of the caprine species. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3013/89 artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 6 kohaselt on esimene ettemakse, mis on liikmesriikidel lubatud l&otilde;ikes 1 m&auml;&auml;ratud piirkondade kitseliha tootjatele maksta, 3,947 ek&uuml;&uuml;d emaskitse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The advance of the specific aid which the Member States are authorized to pay to producers of sheepmeat and goatmeat in less-favoured areas pursuant to Article 1 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 1323/90, within the meaning of Council Directive 75/268/EEC (12), shall be as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> Eriabi ettemakse, mis on liikmesriikidel lubatud n&otilde;ukogu direktiivis 75/268/EM&Uuml; (12) m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses ebasoodsamate piirkondade lamba- ja kitseliha tootjatele maksta vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1323/90 artikli 1 l&otilde;ikele 1, on j&auml;rgmine: </eesti>
<inglise> - ECU 5,977 per ewe in the case of the producers referred to in Article 5 (2) and (4) of the said Regulation, </inglise>
<eesti> - 5,977 ek&uuml;&uuml;d ute kohta nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 5 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 4 osutatud tootjate puhul, </eesti>
<inglise> - ECU 4,130 per ewe in the case of the producers referred to in Article 5 (3) of the said Regulation, </inglise>
<eesti> - 4,130 ek&uuml;&uuml;d ute kohta k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 3 osutatud tootjate puhul, </eesti>
<inglise> - ECU 4,130 per she-goat in the case of the producers referred to in Article 5 (5) of the said Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> - 4,130 ek&uuml;&uuml;d emaskitse kohta nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 5 osutatud tootjate puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Pursuant to Article 13 (3) of Regulation (EEC) No 1601/92, the first advance on the supplementary premium for the 1997 marketing year for producers of light lambs and she-goats in the Canary Islands within the limits provided for in Article 1 (1) of Council Regulation (EEC) No 3493/90 (13) shall be as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1601/92 artikli 13 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt on 1997. majandusaasta t&auml;iendava lisatasu esimene ettemakse kergete tallede ja emaskitsede tootjatele Kanaari saartel vastavalt n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3493/90 (13) artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud piirm&auml;&auml;radele j&auml;rgmine: </eesti>
<inglise> - ECU 2,834 per ewe in the case of producers referred to in Article 5 (3) of that Regulation, </inglise>
<eesti> - 2,834 ek&uuml;&uuml;d ute kohta k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 3 osutatud tootjate puhul, </eesti>
<inglise> - ECU 2,834 per she-goat in the case of producers referred to in Article 5 (5) of that Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> - 2,834 ek&uuml;&uuml;d emaskitse kohta k&otilde;nealuse m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 5 osutatud tootjate puhul. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 6 June 1997. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 6. juuni 1997 </eesti>
